tern of current classes. I'll have to check serialization for `ListBuffer`, especially around its mutability invariants. It's important to properly verify appending and length.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Evaluating JUnit assertions**\\n\\nI’m running into a potential issue with equality in my tests. The `assertEquals(List(\\\"alpha\\\", \\\"beta\\\", \\\"gamma\\\"), restored.toList)` might be problematic since the JUnit assertion is receiving a Scala immutable list compiled with version 2.13 while the runtime uses 2.11. If I compile with a 2.13 library, I need to ensure the classpath resolves correctly. To avoid confusion with Scala collection methods from 2.13, I’ll stick to Java assertions or arrays. Using `assertEquals(\\\"alpha,beta,gamma\\\", restored.mkString(\\\",\\\"))` seems simpler, along with checks for length and appending. I’ll also need to verify empty states.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_tztFrXBAW83R44g6QHz4N6gx|fc_0b8853a5e33c8064016a25620f9b58819693bef9a5abe4bb14", "name": "write", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/org.scala-lang/scala-library/2.11.8/src/test/scala/org_scala_lang/scala_library/ScalaCollectionMutableListBufferTest.scala", "content": "/*\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\n *\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\n */\npackage org_scala_lang.scala_library\n\nimport java.io.ByteArrayInputStream\nimport java.io.ByteArrayOutputStream\nimport java.io.ObjectInputStream\nimport java.io.ObjectOutputStream\n\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Assertions.assertEquals\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Assertions.assertNotSame\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Assertions.assertTrue\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test\n\nimport scala.collection.mutable.ListBuffer\n\nfinal class ScalaCollectionMutableListBufferTest {\n  @Test\n  def serializesMultipleElementsAndRestoresMutableListBuffer(): Unit = {\n    val original: ListBuffer[String] = new ListBuffer[String]()\n    original += \"alpha\"\n    original += \"beta\"\n    original += \"gamma\"\n\n    val restored: ListBuffer[String] = roundTrip(original)\n\n    assertNotSame(original, restored)\n    assertEquals(3, restored.length)\n    assertEquals(\"alpha\", restored(0))\n    assertEquals(\"beta\", restored(1))\n    assertEquals(\"gamma\", restored(2))\n\n    restored += \"delta\"\n    assertEquals(4, restored.length)\n    assertEquals(\"delta\", restored(3))\n  }\n\n  @Test\n  def serializesEmptyBufferAndRestoresAppendableListBuffer(): Unit = {\n    val original: ListBuffer[String] = new ListBuffer[String]()\n\n    val restored: ListBuffer[String] = roundTrip(original)\n\n    assertNotSame(original, restored)\n    assertTrue(restored.isEmpty)\n\n    restored += \"first\"\n    assertEquals(1, restored.length)\n    assertEquals(\"first\", restored(0))\n  }\n\n  private def roundTrip(buffer: ListBuffer[String]): ListBuffer[String] = {\n    val bytes: ByteArrayOutputStream = new ByteArrayOutputStream()\n    val objectOut: ObjectOutputStream = new ObjectOutputStream(bytes)\n    try {\n      objectOut.writeObject(buffer)\n    } finally {\n      objectOut.close()\n    }\n\n    val objectIn: ObjectInputStream = new ObjectInputStream(new ByteArrayInputStream(bytes.toByteArray))\n    try {\n      objectIn.readObject().asInstanceOf[ListBuffer[String]]\n    } finally {\n      objectIn.close()\n    }\n  }\n}\n"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 908, "output": 1132, "cacheRead": 18944, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 20984, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1780834815247, "responseId": "resp_0b8853a5e33c8064016a2561ffb75881969821c905ba6cd98b"}, "toolResults": [{"role": "toolResult", "toolCallId": "call_tztFrXBAW83R44g6QHz4N6gx|fc_0b8853a5e33c8064016a25620f9b58819693bef9a5abe4bb14", "toolName": "wr